<br>
You seem to believe that love and lust are two completely different things.  However, they are the same thing.<br>
<br>
See, there are many different types of love.  There is the love parents have for their children.  There is the love friends have for each other.  There is the love that people have for their spouses.  And there is lust.<br>
<br>
Those who are married know lust.  It is a part of life.  And chances are, most people fall in love AFTER falling in lust.  Why is this?  Because we see people before we know them.<br>
<br>
So, even a one-night stand is, as Kimaya so interestingly put it, a &quot;ritual to Erollisi.&quot;<br>
<br>
Oh, yes.  Before I go, I must say that is an awfully long list of women whom you've supposedly shared a bed with.  So, before you go on about the &quot;harlots of love,&quot; take a look in a mirror some day and see if you do not also deserve to be called a harlot.<br>
<br>
